elf": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/pullrequests/60.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/pull-requests/60"}}, "title": "Improve formatting of vertical (row) header"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/pullrequests/60/comments/100202731.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/pull-requests/60/_/diff#comment-100202731"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 60, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/pullrequests/60.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/pull-requests/60"}}, "title": "Improve formatting of vertical (row) header"}, "content": {"raw": "I bumped the monospaced font size from 7 to 8. 7 looked unreadably small on linux and my windows install, \\(could be that I don\u2019t have a high-DPI screen\\), and I bumped both the header font sizes to 10 on macOS. Hope an increase of one point size doesn\u2019t bother you! Difference for me was from:\n\n\u200c\n\n![](data/bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/1131871613-lyse_too_small.png)\nto\n\n![](data/bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/776311451-lyse_tad_bigger.png)\n\u200c", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I bumped the monospaced font size from 7 to 8. 7 looked unreadably small on linux and my windows install, (could be that I don\u2019t have a high-DPI screen), and I bumped both the header font sizes to 10 on macOS. Hope an increase of one point size doesn\u2019t bother you! Difference for me was from:</p>\n<p>\u200c</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/1131871613-lyse_too_small.png\" />\nto</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/776311451-lyse_tad_bigger.png\" />\n\u200c</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-04-26T20:50:33.688247+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "updated_on": "2019-04-26T20:50:33.694521+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 100202731}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 60, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/pullrequests/60.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/pull-requests/60"}}, "title": "Improve formatting of vertical (row) header"}}, {"update": {"description": "Use monospace font for vertical header, and remove additional space between row number and index string.\r\n\r\nThe `renumber_rows` function left-pads the row numbers so they will be aligned at the period, but this doesn't have the intended effect unless a monospace font is used. Here's a before and after with `integer_indexing = True`:\r\n\r\n![](https://bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/2675465039-sans_vert_header_before.png)\r\n![](https://bitbucket.org/repo/oL84pAo/images/320547339-ubuntu_mono_vert_header.png)", "title": "Improve formatting of vertical (row) header", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "a5e38b9e4c24", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/commit/a5e38b9e4c24.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/commits/a5e38b9e4c24"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}ts=249921"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "lyse", "full_name": "labscript_suite/lyse", "uuid": "{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "4c7723859857", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/rpanderson/lyse/commit/4c7723859857"}, "html": {"href": "#!/rpanderson/lyse/commits/4c7723859857"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/rpanderson/lyse"}, "html": {"href": "#!/rpanderson/lyse"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{af3f4037-4cb2-49dd-b675-22e0ce6522c4}ts=2203673"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "lyse", "full_name": "rpanderson/lyse", "uuid": "{af3f4037-4cb2-49dd-b675-22e0ce6522c4}"}, "branch": {"name": "header_formatting"}}, "state": "MERGED", "author": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "date": "2019-04-26T20:46:36.799049+00:00"}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 60, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/pullrequests/60.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/pull-requests/60"}}, "title": "Improve formatting of vertical (row) header"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/pullrequests/60/comments/99917632.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/pull-requests/60/_/diff#comment-99917632"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 60, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/pullrequests/60.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/pull-requests/60"}}, "title": "Improve formatting of vertical (row) header"}, "content": {"raw": "Just checked what this looked like on macOS. For some whenever we set explicit font sizes in macOS, they come out looking smaller than on other OSs. Hence why the outputbox has a font size that depends on the OS.\n\nHere\u2019s what this change looks like:\n\n![](data/bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/2024146306-lyse_7_8.png)\nIt\u2019s a bit tiny. How about bumping both header font sizes up by 2pt each? That\u2019s what I decided on for the OutputBox: it is  11pt on Windows and Linux, and 13pt on macOS - this ended up looking about the same size relative to other UI elements.\n\nSo you would want something like:\n\n```\n        font.setPointSize(10 if sys.platform == 'darwin' else 8)\n        self._header.setFont(font)\n        font.setPointSize(9 if sys.platform == 'darwin' else 7)\n        font.setFamily('Ubuntu Mono')\n        self._vertheader.setFont(font)\n```\n\nAnd then it looks more like:\n\n![](data/bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/3639805373-lyse_9_10.png)\nSo slightly more readable.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Just checked what this looked like on macOS. For some whenever we set explicit font sizes in macOS, they come out looking smaller than on other OSs. Hence why the outputbox has a font size that depends on the OS.</p>\n<p>Here\u2019s what this change looks like:</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/2024146306-lyse_7_8.png\" />\nIt\u2019s a bit tiny. How about bumping both header font sizes up by 2pt each? That\u2019s what I decided on for the OutputBox: it is  11pt on Windows and Linux, and 13pt on macOS - this ended up looking about the same size relative to other UI elements.</p>\n<p>So you would want something like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>        font.setPointSize(10 if sys.platform == &#39;darwin&#39; else 8)\n        self._header.setFont(font)\n        font.setPointSize(9 if sys.platform == &#39;darwin&#39; else 7)\n        font.setFamily(&#39;Ubuntu Mono&#39;)\n        self._vertheader.setFont(font)\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>And then it looks more like:</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/3639805373-lyse_9_10.png\" />\nSo slightly more readable.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-04-25T03:17:11.369831+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "updated_on": "2019-04-25T03:17:11.377311+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 99917632}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 60, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/pullrequests/60.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/pull-requests/60"}}, "title": "Improve formatting of vertical (row) header"}}, {"update": {"description": "Use monospace font for vertical header, and remove additional space between row number and index string.\r\n\r\nThe `renumber_rows` function left-pads the row numbers so they will be aligned at the period, but this doesn't have the intended effect unless a monospace font is used. Here's a before and after with `integer_indexing = True`:\r\n\r\n![](https://bitbucket.org/repo/BMBAeq/images/2675465039-sans_vert_header_before.png)\r\n![](https://bitbucket.org/repo/oL84pAo/images/320547339-ubuntu_mono_vert_header.png)", "title": "Improve formatting of vertical (row) header", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "a5e38b9e4c24", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lys